dcterms:description: Stained MNIST is a set of handwritten digits from MNIST, modified to have high resolution and thinner writings, with dot stains added around the digits. The dataset is designed to compare the performance of the proposed RED algorithm against existing algorithms on images with high-resolution settings.
dcterms:title: Stained MNIST

dcterms:description: The Diabetic Retinopathy Screening Dataset is used for detecting abnormalities from fundus photographs, which are generally high resolution and noisy. The dataset is publicly available on Kaggle and is used to evaluate the performance of the RED model in the context of diabetic retinopathy screening.
dcterms:title: Diabetic Retinopathy Screening Dataset
